-- RBS, Lloyds Annual Bonuses Capped for a Fourth Time, Sky Reports
-- B y   C h r i s   S p i l l a n e
-- 2013-01-06T14:16:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-06/rbs-lloyds-annual-bonuses-capped-for-a-fourth-time-sky-reports.html
Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc  and
 Lloyds (LLOY)  Banking Group Plc plan to cap staff bonuses for a fourth
straight year, Sky News reported without saying where it got the
information.  The banks, part-owned by the U.K. government, will impose a
2,000-pound ($3,200) ceiling on the payouts, the news
organization said. Spokeswomen for Lloyds and RBS declined to
comment on the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Spillane in  London  at 
 cspillane3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at 
 ablackman@bloomberg.net  